        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 1:53PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 153 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Saint Francis, or near Piggott, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saint Francis, Valley Ridge, Providence, St. Francis, Campbell,
Morris State Park, Wilhelmina, Chalk Bluff Natural Area, Clarkton,
Piggott, Chalk Bluff Battlefield Park, Baird, Pollard, McGuires,
Townley, Malden, and Holcomb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for eastern
Arkansas...and southeastern Missouri.</instruction>
